definition.value: This is an AE which is an inflammation of the choroid (thin pigmented vascular coat of the eye) and retina of the eye caused by cytomegalovirus .
This is an AE which is a medical condition in which damage occurs to the retina due to diabetes mellitus.
This is an AE which is the simultaneous perception of two images of a single object that may be displaced horizontally or vertically in relation to each other.
This is an AE which is a lack of coordination of movement typified by the undershoot or overshoot of intended position with the hand, arm, leg, or eye. It is a type of ataxia.
This is an AE which is a neuropsychological condition that causes a distortion of perception.
This is an AE which is less common but nonetheless a possible reason as to why a patient may fail the 4 PRT.
This is an AE which may be a manifestation of a variety of isolated ocular or systemic diseases in children.
This is an AE which is a visual disturbance in which objects appear with a red hue, is a recognized phenomenon after surgical excision of the natural lens.
This is an AE which is sometimes visible deposits within the eye's vitreous humour ("the vitreous"), which is normally transparent, or between the vitreous and retina.
This is an AE which is a visual disturbance in which objects in the visual field appear to oscillate.
This is an AE which is the phenomenon of seeing light without light entering the eye.
This is an AE which is a scratch to the surface of the cornea of the eye.
This is an AE which is a collection of pus that has built up within the tissue of the corneal.
This is an AE which is severe enough to require corneal transplantation is a rare complication of uveitis.
This is an AE which is deterioration in the medical sense on the corneal.
This is an AE which is the transparent front part of the eye that covers the iris, pupil, and anterior chamber.

This is an AE which refers to anything that interferes with the cornea's stromal architecture, contributes to blood vessel migration, increases corneal pigmentation, or predisposes to corneal edema, disrupts the corneas transparency.
This is an AE which is a group of rare hereditary disorders characterised by bilateral abnormal deposition of substances in the transparent front part of the eye called the cornea.
This is an AE which is a single layer of endothelial cells on the inner surface of the cornea.

This is an AE which is made up of epithelial tissue and covers the front of the cornea and acts as a barrier to protect the cornea, resisting the free flow of fluids from the tears, and prevents bacteria from entering the epithelium and corneal stroma.
This is an AE which is a disorder of the eyes characterized by the failure of the cornea's outermost layer of epithelial cells to attach to the underlying basement membrane (Bowman's layer).
This is an AE which is an age-related disease in which abnormal fibrillar extracellular material is produced and accumulates in many ocular tissues.

This is an AE which comprises a sequence of complex immune responses that involves the recognition of the foreign histocompatibility antigens of the corneal graft by the host's immune system, leading to the initiation of the immune response cascade.
This is an AE which is any damage or abnormal change in the corneal tissue of an organism, usually caused by disease or trauma.
This is an AE which is the in-growth of new blood vessels from the pericorneal plexus into avascular corneal tissue as a result of oxygen deprivation.
This is an AE which is a common sign of acute or protracted corneal disease of various aetiologies.
This is an AE which is a transparent membrane which allows light to pass through it.
This is an AE which accumulate in reaction to inflammatory responses and remain permanently in corneal stroma, and conventionally correctable only by donor corneal transplantation.
This is an AE which is the transparent front part of the eye that covers the iris, pupil, and anterior chamber and its is a process of becoming thin.
This is an AE which is a  type of anterior uveitis and  inflammation of iris and the ciliary body with inflammation predominantly confined to ciliary body.
This is an AE which is fibrous bands that form between iris tissues and organs,often as a result of injury during surgery.
This is an AE which is a hole in one of the structures of the eye, such as the iris.
This is an AE which is part of the eye and its functiuon gets disorder.
This is an AE which is characterized specifically as an area of iris skin becoming lighter than the baseline skin color, but not completely devoid of pigment.
This is an AE which is damage to the iris caused by an external force.
This is an AE which is the inflammation of the uvea, the pigmented layer that lies between the inner retina and the outer fibrous layer composed of the sclera and cornea.
This is an AE which is due to the lens cortex (outer layer) becoming opaque and they occur when changes in the fluid contained in the periphery of the lens causes fissuring.
This is an AE which is the most common type of cataract, and involves the central or 'nuclear' part of the lens.

This is an AE which is cloudy at the back of the lens adjacent to the capsule (or bag) in which the lens sits and  because light becomes more focused toward the back of the lens, they can cause disproportionate symptoms for their size.
This is an AE which is a tissue that lines the inside of the eyelids and covers the sclera (the white of the eye) and it has deposit.
This is an AE which refers to a small spherical group of cells containing a cavity on the conjunctival.
This is an AE which is the increase of blood flow to different tissues in the conjunctial tissue.
This is an AE which is a conjunctival state of inflammation or painful reaction to allergy or cell-lining damage.
This is an AE which is the swelling (or edema) of the conjunctiva.
This is an AE which is a decrease in the total amount of red blood cells (RBCs) or hemoglobin in the blood or a lowered ability of the blood to carry oxygen.
This is an AE which is an eye finding occurring early in leptospirosis, which is caused by Leptospira interrogans.
This is an AE which is an inflammatory or, more seriously, infective condition of the cornea involving disruption of its epithelial layer with involvement of the corneal stroma.
This is an AE which is inflammation of the conjunctiva (the membrane covering the white part of the eye) due to allergy.
This is an AE which causes the rapid onset of conjunctival redness, swelling of the eyelid, and a sticky discharge.
This is an AE which is often associated with an infection of the upper respiratory tract, a common cold, or a sore throat.
